    <!-- Chosen Palette: Minimalist Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A thematic, single-page scrolling website designed to guide potential clients through a compelling narrative. It starts with a bold Hero section stating the value proposition, moves to outline the 'Problem' with traditional photoshoots, presents Finaura as the 'Solution', explains the 'Process' in simple steps, provides powerful proof in an interactive 'Showcase' with before-and-after sliders, lists the key 'Benefits', shows the 'Use Cases', and ends with a clear 'Call to Action'. This structure was chosen over a direct report mimicry because it creates a persuasive marketing funnel, educating and convincing the user step-by-step, culminating in the interactive portfolio which is the most critical conversion tool. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Hero/Problem/Promise Sections: Goal: Inform/Persuade. Method: Large typography and concise, bold statements using HTML/Tailwind. Interaction: Subtle text animations on scroll. Justification: Grabs attention and quickly communicates the core business value.
        - Process Section: Goal: Explain. Method: A numbered, 3-step visual guide using an HTML list styled with Tailwind to create distinct cards. Interaction: Elements fade in on scroll. Justification: Breaks down the process into easily digestible steps, making it seem simple and efficient.
        - Showcase Section: Goal: Compare/Demonstrate. Method: An interactive before-and-after image comparison slider for multiple examples. Built with two overlapping images in an HTML container. Interaction: User can click and drag a handle to reveal the 'after' image. This is the centerpiece. Justification: Provides tangible, interactive proof of the service's quality and is far more engaging than static images. Library/Method: Vanilla JavaScript for slider logic.
        - Benefits/Use Cases: Goal: Reinforce value. Method: A grid of cards with HTML/Tailwind, each with an icon (Unicode) and text. Interaction: Hover effects. Justification: A clean, scannable format for summarizing key selling points.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
